## Permission Best Practices

### When to Request

- [ ] After user has seen value (e.g., completed onboarding, used core feature)
- [ ] In context (e.g., "Enable notifications to get order updates")
- [ ] Not on first launch unless critical (e.g., messaging app)
- [ ] One request; if denied, do not repeatedly prompt

### Permission States

| State | Action |
|-------|--------|
| Not determined | Show in-app explanation, then request |
| Denied | Respect; show "Enable in Settings" only when relevant |
| Granted | Register for remote notifications |
| Provisional (iOS) | Delivered quietly; user can promote to full |

### Pre-Permission UX

- [ ] Explain benefit before system dialog
- [ ] Use custom modal or inline message
- [ ] Link to Settings only when user has denied and feature needs it
- [ ] Do not dark-pattern (fake buttons, misleading copy)

